         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Sale ¶ Sep 13 1879 ¶ My dear Sir Ferdinand ¶  ¶ I must apologize for a seeming neglect in not before now acknowledging your kind present of the first two decades of your Atlas of the Eucalypts. ¶  I h...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">79.09.13</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Alfred Howitt</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M11, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Eucalyptus cephalocarpa</seg> (MEL 1606637). MS annotations by M: '<seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">Euc. cinerea</hi>
                     </seg>', 'E. pulverulenta' and 'Answ 14/9/79'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>Sale<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Vic.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Sep 13 1879</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir Ferdinand</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I must apologize for a seeming neglect in not before now acknowledging your kind present of the first two decades of your Atlas of the Eucalypts.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B79.13.11, Decades 1, 2.</p>
               </note> I have examined it with the greatest interest — its value here and at home will be extremely appreciated.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am now commencing to collect for you a series of E. Risdoni &amp;c. of which I send you herewith the first example.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Trees under 50 ft — scraggy and with scanty foliage. Bark thick, fibrous out to the small branches. Seedlings oval opposite leaves set at short intervals. Foliage similar on the tree but the young shoots and some of the older ones have elongated leaves. This example grows in a rather swampy piece of ground — sandy clay — about 9 miles from Stratford<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Vic.</p>
               </note> on the Bairnsdale Road.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">yours faithfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A W Howitt</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">P.S. I feel highly honored at your proposal to name a new Eucalypt after me<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Eucalyptus howittiana</seg>, B82.08.04, p. 172.</p>
               </note> and will collect further examples of it from Castleburn, Dargo and Ensay.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">All Vic.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eucalyptus%20risdoni%20">Eucalyptus risdoni </name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
